Our comprehensive emergency response plan is designed to protect our employees, environment and the community and, among other things, requires that:

 oAll nonessential personnel immediately exit the area affected by the release;

 oKraft immediately notify local officials, requesting their assistance, if necessary;

For a release that leaves the Kraft site, the company would work with local officials to notify neighbors so that appropriate safety precautions could be taken. If ammonia is in the outside atmosphere, the safest place to be is indoors with windows and doors shut and the ventilation system turned off.
